terally took off.\", \"from\": 2671, \"to\": 2778, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2733, \"end\": 2741, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jalal_Hosseini\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Hosseini\", \"types\": [\"Q937857\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jalal_Hosseini\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jalal_Hosseini\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a support structure\", \"from\": 2685, \"to\": 2704}, {\"ngram\": \"Fasihi's career\", \"from\": 2743, \"to\": 2758}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She participated in the World Athletics Indoor Championships, where the relatively unknown runner scorched the track with a sensational entry record time of 7.29 seconds in the 60-metre sprint held in Belgrade, Serbia.\", \"from\": 2780, \"to\": 2998, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2804, \"end\": 2840, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics_Indoor_Championships\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.430059618725981e-31, \"text\": \"World Athletics Indoor Championships\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics_Indoor_Championships\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics_Indoor_Championships\"}, {\"begin\": 2981, \"end\": 2989, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgrade\", \"score\": 0.999999999998181, \"rank\": 1.4632224482639606e-12, \"text\": \"Belgrade\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgrade\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgrade\"}, {\"begin\": 2991, \"end\": 2997, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia\", \"score\": 0.9989554815219415, \"rank\": 0.0010173376187773697, \"text\": \"Serbia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the relatively unknown runner\", \"from\": 2848, \"to\": 2877}, {\"ngram\": \"the track\", \"from\":